The paper discusses the usability issues of Voice User Interfaces, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The study focuses on identifying mechanisms that underpin coordinated collective vocal behavior, which involves simulation and control, indicating the relevance of the sub-categories of System Dynamics (cs.SD) and Control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the implications of vocal interactivity in the animal kingdom, which relates to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for further investigation of key control variables, which falls under the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL).
